'''Mintiper Moonsilver''' was a [[bard]] and [[adventurer]] of the [[North]], as well as a member of the [[Harpers]], in the mid-to-late 14{{th}} century [[DR]]. His works were collected in [[Silverymoon]] and compiled into ''[[Mintiper's Chapbook]]''.<ref>{{Cite web/Mintiper's Chapbook/Part 1}} 
{{Quote|By night dark dreams bring me much pain—but always comes, after, bright morning again.|Mintiper Moonsilver, ''[[Nine Stars Around a Silver Moon]]'', {{Yearlink|1336}}}}
{{TOC limit|3}}
